item.dc:creator: @Lagex Lagex
item.description:
@Lagex wrote:

When you don’t have enough brackets (} or {), the file cannot run, because Java doesn’t recognize it.

You need ATLEAST 3 }'s at the end of the client.java.

I hope this helps. If you are having trouble, paste this at the very bottom:

[code] }
}

}[/code]

If it says: enum expected remove some brackets!

item.dc:creator: @Tico135 Tico
item.description:
@Tico135 wrote:

When you reach the end of the file without parsing it means that you have forgotten to place a bracket at the end of the code. Add brackets one by one and compile after you add one bracket. If you get a ‘class interface or enum expected’ error, that means there are too many brackets, in which case you will have to remove one.
